---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home" current="home">
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="hero__eyebrow">Comparative environmental &amp; industrial strategy</p>
    <h1>Balanced development where resources are not yet fully commercialized</h1>
    <p>
      This portal structures deep research comparing <strong>Lommel, Belgium</strong> — a century of
      high-purity silica extraction, industrial clustering, ecological reclamation, and renewable
      energy co-location — with <strong>Uganda’s</strong> documented mineral endowment, especially
      Lake Victoria glass sands and broader development minerals.
    </p>
    <p>
      Content is designed for academic work (including doctoral research): every page links to a
      curated bibliography; quantitative claims require a cited source. The framework report is
      available as PDF and is broken into navigable sections on this site.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="/documents/Lommel_Uganda_Sustainable_Resource_Management_Report.pdf">Download framework PDF</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid-2">
    <a class="card card--link" href="/lommel">
      <h2>Lommel case study</h2>
      <p>Zilverzand, Sibelco, Lommelse Sahara restoration, Kristal Solar Park, and Floating PV at Mol/Dessel — with fact-check notes.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card card--link" href="/uganda">
      <h2>Uganda analysis</h2>
      <p>Silica deposits, import dependency, lacustrine risks, and parallels to the “Lommel model” of local value addition.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card card--link" href="/catalog">
      <h2>Resource catalog</h2>
      <p>Editable JSON catalog: silica, limestone, kaolin, salt, dimension stone, geothermal, and more — expand via GitHub.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card card--link" href="/roadmap">
      <h2>Policy roadmap</h2>
      <p>Reclamation bonds, green industrial clusters, and circular glass — three pillars from the framework report.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card card--link" href="/bibliography">
      <h2>Bibliography</h2>
      <p>DGSM, DELVE, BGS/NORA, Ugandan legislation, Lommel municipal sources, IRENA, and Sibelco FPV.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="card card--link" href="/methodology">
      <h2>Methodology</h2>
      <p>How we avoid unsourced claims; how to add data through the repository for Netlify deploys.</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <div class="notice">
    <strong>Repository status:</strong> GitHub repo
    <a href="https://github.com/Explodingding/uganda">Explodingding/uganda</a> is ready for your first push.
    Connect it to Netlify for automatic builds on each commit (see README).
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
